commit.message:
Fix memory leak in mkd_xml()

The Cstring |f| wasn't being DELETE()d before returning from mkd_xml(),
leading to a leak every time it was called.
up to v3.0.0d
it's not an email address if it starts with a '@'
I put the --container check (in the librarian maker) in the wrong place!
add the --container config option so a ldconfig won't be installed into librarian.sh
add a test case for >%class1 class2%
allow multiple classes for >% blocks
replace an include of strings.h w string.h
make tools/rep.c fancier by expanding backslash escapes; add a crash test for a #header line with a bucketload of trailing spaces
fix a bug in tab expansion where I was lazy, assumed that T() strings would always be null-terminated, but didn't null terminate the resulting string after a tab expansion
left an argument out of main.c's memory deallocator callback
up to version 3.0.0c
update the callback creation functions to use the proper arguments
okay, the whole callback structure was a hot mess;  change it so that every different callback has its own date & free function
set the version to 3.0.0b
fix a handful of places where I either didn't guard against underflows or null pointers; add test cases for them in crash.t
fix some brokenness in markdown extra footnotes that made adjacent footnotes not render properly
add the new runtime flag ALT_AS_TITLE; if an image has no title, use the alt text as the title
add config.sed to the list of config files (to avoid HILARIOUS errors if I simply rsync a discount to a different machine
up to v 3.0.0a

fix code indentation in a test program in configure; tweak title
generation in xmlpage to stop gcc & clang from complaining about
dangling elses

Make C99 clean

* Clang 16 (and likely GCC 14) will enforce strict C99 semantics
  and break old K&R C declarations and require correct C89
  function prototypes.

Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/870952
Clang: https://discourse.llvm.org/t/configure-script-breakage-with-the-new-werror-implicit-function-declaration/65213/9
add a new testcase to verify that -> ... <- works properly
start tweaking in preprocessor support; start with a rough m4 framework
have all of the extensions code guarded by checking against MKD_STRICT
match the descriptions for MKD_STRICT in mkdio.h.in & markdown.h
hunt down and remove all references to the NORELAXED flag (now STRICT)
add a fistful of test cases for the new! improved! Markdown.pl compatible <tags>
